  "texts": [
    "The original plan for the KiDS survey, as endorsed by ESO's Public Surveys Panel in 2005, was to cover 1500 square degrees in ugri-bands with the VST (de Jong et al. 2013).",
    "This proposed area is shown in Fig. 3 as the full span of coloured tiles.",
    "Subsequently, in 2006, ESO approved the VIKING survey (Edge et al. 2013), which would add five NIR filters to the same proposed survey area.",
    "The observations for KiDS and VIKING started in 2011 and 2009, respectively, soon after their corresponding telescopes were commissioned.",
    "Fig. 4.4Fig."
  ],
